  "text": "Kubernetes API deprecation policy enforcement is implemented across multiple key files in the apiserver and apiextensions-apiserver packages:\n\n## Core Deprecation Logic\n\nThe foundation of API deprecation enforcement resides in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go`. This file implements three critical functions:\n\n1. **IsDeprecated()** - Determines if an API object is deprecated by checking if it implements the `apiLifecycleDeprecated` interface and comparing the deprecation version against the current API server version.\n\n2. **RemovedRelease()** - Extracts the removal version in \"major.minor\" format from objects that implement the `apiLifecycleRemoved` interface. This indicates when an API will no longer be served.\n\n3. **WarningMessage()** - Generates human-readable deprecation warnings that include the deprecated version, removal version (if applicable), and replacement API information.\n\n4. **MajorMinor()** - Parses semantic versioning from the API server's version info to enable proper version comparisons.\n\nThese functions rely on three interfaces defined in the same file:\n- `apiLifecycleDeprecated`: Returns major/minor deprecation version\n- `apiLifecycleRemoved`: Returns major/minor removal version  \n- `apiLifecycleReplacement`: Returns the replacement GroupVersionKind\n\n## Warning Injection at Request Handling\n\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go`, the deprecation functions are called during API resource handler registration (lines 788-795). The `registerResourceHandlers()` method checks each API version to determine if it's deprecated and extracts its removal version, then passes these flags to `InstrumentRouteFunc()`.\n\n## Metrics and Audit Annotation\n\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go` file implements the warning delivery mechanism:\n\n1. **InstrumentRouteFunc()** wraps REST handlers to capture deprecation information\n2. **MonitorRequest()** processes each request and:\n   - Records a deprecation gauge metric with labels including the removal release (line 592)\n   - Adds audit annotations using the constant `deprecatedAnnotationKey = \"k8s.io/deprecated\"` set to \"true\"\n   - Adds `removedReleaseAnnotationKey = \"k8s.io/removed-release\"` annotation with the target removal version (lines 593-596)\n3. Warnings are added to HTTP responses via `utilwarning.AddWarningsHandler()` in installer.go\n\n## Version Availability Control\n\nThe minimum supported API version and served version checks are enforced through the CustomResourceDefinition versioning system in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go` and `types.go`. Each `CustomResourceDefinitionVersion` has a `Served` boolean field (line 175) that gates whether that version is available via REST APIs.\n\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go`:\n\n1. **hasServedCRDVersion()** (lines 1394-1399) checks if a version has its `Served` flag enabled\n2. **defaultDeprecationWarning()** (lines 1070-1087) generates default warnings for deprecated versions, recommending the newest served non-deprecated version\n3. The discovery system only exposes versions where `Served: true`, preventing access to removed API versions\n\n## Autogenerated Lifecycle Methods\n\nAPI objects throughout kubernetes/kubernetes include autogenerated `APILifecycleDeprecated()` and `APILifecycleRemoved()` methods in files matching pattern `zz_generated.prerelease-lifecycle.go`. These are generated from `k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen` tags in type definitions (e.g., `//+k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:deprecated=1.9` and `//+k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:removed=1.16`).\n\nThis enforcement chain ensures that:\n- Deprecated API versions receive clear warnings to clients\n- Removal versions are tracked and audited\n- Removed API versions are not served (through the `Served: false` flag)\n- The apiserver maintains minimum supported version compliance through the deprecation policy\n"
